==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang}} {{term|þunor|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|þunraz|lang=gem-pro}}, from *þen, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|(s)tenh₂-||to thunder|lang=ine-pro}}. Germanic cognates include West Frisian {{term|tonger|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|donder|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Donner|lang=de}}. Other cognates include [[w:Persian language|Persian]] {{fa-Arab|[[تندر]]}} (tondar), Latin {{term|tono|tonō|lang=la}}.

